entry.title: [ios] Add missing dependencies on swift_source_set(...) targets
entry.content:
When running `gn check ...` the Objective-C header generated from

the Swift source by the Swift compiler is ignored by gn and thus

the corresponding dependency is not reported if missing. This can

lead to flaky build (or build considered as dirty).



This CL adds the missing dependencies. They were found by changing

the template swift_source_set(...) to declare a secondary target

listing the generated file as input, running `gn check ...` and

fixing the errors.



Note: eventually the bug in `gn check ...` should be fixed, but

this CL is improving the situation and should land before the

underlying issue is fixed.

entry.title: [ios] Implement unified BookmarkModel instance behind flag
entry.content:
Behavioral changes only behind disabled feature flag.



This patch uses `syncer::kEnableBookmarkFoldersForAccountStorage`, which

is disabled by default, to determine whether there should be a single

BookmarkModel instance per BrowserState (if flag enabled) or whether

there should be two of them (if flag disabled).



The design principle is that the flag is, barring a few exceptions,

implemented inside the three existing bookmark-related factories on iOS.

The publicly-observable API and behavior behind these factories does not

change depending on the feature flag, but internally the plumbing

changes significantly.



A key piece that makes this possible is the newly-introduced class

`LegacyBookmarkModelWithSharedUnderlyingModel`, which is able to expose

a split view (i.e. subset of a larger BookmarkModel instance). Most of

the functionality is included in this patch, except for observer

handling which will be tackled in follow-up patches, as well as more

advanced needs like dealing with null permanent folders.



Design doc (sorry, Googlers only):

https://docs.google.com/document/d/11Dm4-FWEpT_fgxfAeq16O8qxOtaOZbU2o3MZeHDByUM/edit?usp=sharing

entry.title: [DataSharing] Add platform-agnostic group-related API skeleton
entry.content:
This CL adds new methods (not yet implemented) to DataSharingService,

that provides API to access/edit group data, needed to implement the UI

and maybe few other things. Java counterpart is to be added in a follow

up.



DataSharingService diverges from SDK:

1. Most of the methods work with singular, e.g. there is no batch group

editing operations. This likely suits all our needs and slightly simpler

to use.

2. API uses dedicated data structures, decoupling them early from DB

protos (coming soon) and SDK protos should give us more flexibility in

the future in case we prefer to diverge from them more.

3. Instead of using single UpdateGroup(Action), there are dedicated

methods, such as AddMember()/RemoveMember(). The reasoning is similar

to 1., on top of that this makes API more constrained -> perhaps harder

to misuse / better compile-time checks.

entry.title: Mojo cpp bindings generator: avoid redundant version checks.
entry.content:
Previously, the variable `last_checked_version` doesn't work

as expected. The scoping behavior of Jinja prevents variable

update from persisting across for-loop runs. As a result,

generated struct validation code has a version check for

each field whose min_version > 0, even when there are

multiple fields belonging to the same version:



```

if (object->header_.version < 31)

return true;

if (!mojo::internal::ValidateStruct(object->foo, validation_context))

return false;



if (object->header_.version < 31)

return true;

if (!mojo::internal::ValidateStruct(object->bar, validation_context))

return false;

```



This CL uses a namespace object to fix that.

StylableSelect behind a new "bikeshed" value for the appearance

style rules or not would cause circular style and would at least require

entry.title: Skip static animations on compositor and main
entry.content:
An animation with empty keyframes or with keyframes whose property

values are identical between frames previously ran as a normal

animation. As there is no visual change other than at a phase boundary,

these animations do not need to run on the compositor, and only need

to be scheduled on the main thread at phase boundaries.



This is the first step in optimizing no-op animations. A follow up

patch will short-circuit sampling when the property value is constant.

Another patch will refine the rules for background color compositing

to only consider dynamic properties. Finally, metrics will be added

to track shorthand expansion of CSS properties, which is likely the

most common source of static properties in CSS animations.

entry.title: [iOS][PageInfo] Update security info after full load
entry.content:
If the user opens page info while the page is being loaded, its

certificates might have not loaded yet and so the page is insecure. This

results in page info forever showing that the page is insecure even if

it's not. This CL fixes it by making the view controller request for an

update of the security description if it hasn't been fully loaded.



We also make sure that the security subpage uses the same description as

the root of page info. Previously, because the security subpage was

fetching the security information by itself, the security status could

be different if 1) page info is opened before certificates are loaded

and 2) security subpage is opened after the certificates are loaded.



Fixed: b:327589441, b:328370587

entry.title: [ios] Decouple LegacyBookmarkModel from BookmarkModel
entry.content:
No behavioral changes, pure refactoring.



The general idea is that LegacyBookmarkModel becomes an independent

interface that (currently) simply wraps BookmarkModel, with a more

narrow API. In upcoming patches, another subclass will be introduced

that operates under a shared underlying BookmarkModel instead of

always owning a dedicated instance.



For the handful of cases were the new interface (LegacyBookmarkModel)

isn't sufficient, a side channel is introduced in the factories,

GetDedicatedUnderlyingModelForBrowserState(). This is a subtle API and

one that will, in upcoming patches, require callers to implement

flag-guarding.



Test helpers are trivially forked from components/bookmarks/test, as

the interface is analogous but the code itself cannot be shared.



The patch also includes various test-only fixes such as

verifyBookmarksWithTitle() previously doing something else other than

what the name suggests (namely, match the query against the URL).



Design doc (sorry, Googlers only):

https://docs.google.com/document/d/11Dm4-FWEpT_fgxfAeq16O8qxOtaOZbU2o3MZeHDByUM/edit?usp=sharing

entry.content:
TabDragDropDelegate starts capturing gesture events when the user starts

dragging a tab from WebUI tabstrip. Currently it only stops the capture

entry.title: Revert "WebGL and PaintCanvasVideoRenderer: Don't discard color space"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 63aab357d61b1e64b5ccd165b2d71caf65f1bdfb.



Reason for revert: Broke chromium/ci/mac(11|12|13)-arm64-rel-tests

https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/mac11-arm64-rel-tests/34998/overview



Original change's description:

> WebGL and PaintCanvasVideoRenderer: Don't discard color space

>

> Behavior change:

>

> When UNPACK_COLORSPACE_CONVERSION_WEBGL is BROWSER_DEFAULT_WEBGL,

> this fixes uploads from HTMLVideoElement and VideoFrame to match the

> WebGL spec and convert to the unpackColorSpace. If it is NONE, then

> preserve the existing Chromium behavior of dropping the color space

> information. This is not what the spec says to do but it is what all

> other browsers do.

>

> This will not change the behavior of using Rec709 video (far and away

> the most common video color space) with an unpackColorSpace of srgb

> (the default and also far and away the most common value). For other

> combinations, this is likely to change behavior.

>

> Code change:

>

> In PaintCanvasVideoRenderer::UpdateLastImage we sometimes use the

> right color space (e.g, when creating the SharedImage) and sometimes

> don't (e.g, when specifying the SkImageInfo for that image), resulting

> in color space information mostly being dropped on the floor.

>

> Fix this by using the same color space information in all of

> PaintCanvasVideoRenderer. Use the existing compatibility helper

> function GetVideoFrameRGBColorSpacePreferringSRGB, but move it into

> VideoFrame for use elsewhere.

>

> In WebGLRenderingContextBase::TexImageHelperMediaVideoFrame, fix the

> places where we would fail to specify the SkColorSpace in an

> SkImageInfo. Replace unpack_color_space_is_srgb with

> needs_rgb_color_conversion, because that is what is being checked.

>

> For HTMLVideoElement and VideoFrame, if

> UNPACK_COLORSPACE_CONVERSION_WEBGL is NONE then preserve the

> existing behavior of dropping the color space information.

>

entry.title: arc: Files: Introduce cmdline switch to always mount Android volumes
entry.content:
Android volumes (Play files in ARC++ container and DocumentsProviders)

are mounted only when IsArcPlayStoreEnabled() returns true, which forces

entry.title: Apply AlignUpRefCountSizeForApple workaround for both macOS and iOS.
entry.content:
macOS added AlignUpRefCountSizeForMac as a workaround for a crash.

iOS is seeing similar crashes also related to swift as in

crbug/40066367, so apply the workaround to both platforms.



There is some evidence this is related to Swift's implementation of

__StringStorage.create, which will round up the total allocation to a

malloc bucket estimate (16 bytes) and claim any excess capacity as

additional code unit capacity. For large allocations, malloc_size is

consulted and any excess capacity is likewise claimed as additional

code unit capacity. This may be worth further investigation in

crbug/327804972

entry.title: [AriaNotify] Allow queuing notifications in HandleAriaNotification
entry.content:
Previously, whenever an author performed multiple calls to `ariaNotify`,

the notifications produced from this method would be overwritten, only

the last notification would be serialized to `AXNodeData`.



To correct this behavior, this change allows these notifications to be

queued in `HandleAriaNotification` to be serialized all at once later.



Note that the serialization code in `ax_object.cc` still overrides the

notification attributes in `AXNodeData`, this will be updated in later

patches to correctly store a list of attributes instead.
